  "slug": "plain-scones",
  "title": "Plain scones",
  "subtitle": "Classic British cream tea scones",
  "excerpt": "Scones need a hot oven, cold butter, and minimal handling. Overworking the dough develops the gluten and makes them tough; the less you touch the dough, the better they rise. Cut with a sharp cutter in one straight-down press, not twisted.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Scones are a British quick bread, documented from at least the early nineteenth century in Scottish and English domestic cookery. Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136, scones appear in the bread chapter as a quick-rise baked good leavened with baking powder. The cream tea pairing with clotted cream and jam is documented from the late Victorian period.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The rise in a scone comes from two things: baking powder and the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "rubbing in",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpb82lc70000p0v4dimil9ra"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " of cold butter. Work quickly so the butter stays cold, and stop mixing as soon as the dough comes together, even a minute of extra kneading flattens them.",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "type": "tip"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "Twist the cutter as you press down and the sides seal against themselves, blocking the rise. Press straight down and lift straight up for the tallest scones.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
