      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C (200°C fan). Sift {{self-raising-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{salt-table}} into a large bowl. Rub in {{unsalted-butter}} until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Stir in {{caster-sugar}}. Pour in nearly all the {{whole-milk}} and mix quickly to a soft, slightly sticky dough. Turn onto a floured surface and pat out to about 3 cm thick, do not roll. Stamp out rounds with a 6 cm cutter, pressing straight down without twisting. Re-pat the trimmings and cut again.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Glaze and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place on a lined baking tray, close together but not touching. Brush the tops with beaten {{eggs}}, keep the glaze off the sides or it will anchor the scone to the tray and stop it rising. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until risen and deep gold on top. Eat within a few hours of baking.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
